SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS FOR INDIGENOUS CULTURAL AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

Users of this resource are reminded to respect Indigenous Cultural and Intellectual Property (ICIP) rights and to follow the CARE Principles for Indigenous Data Governance:
- Collective Benefit
- Authority to Control
- Responsibility
- Ethics

When applying these patterns and principles in research contexts involving Indigenous data, knowledge, or communities, please ensure appropriate consultation and adherence to Indigenous data sovereignty principles.
